  <title>Truco Mineiro</title>
  <p>In Truco Mineiro, there are <strong>fixed Manilhas</strong> (the strongest cards in the game). No "Vira" card is dealt.</p>
  
  <section id="hierarchy">
    <title>Card Hierarchy</title>
    <p>The hierarchy is fixed as follows (strongest to weakest):</p>
    <list>
        <item><p><media type="image" src="figures/4_of_clubs.svg" width="80"/> <strong>4 of Clubs (Zap)</strong> - The strongest card.</p></item>
        <item><p><media type="image" src="figures/7_of_hearts.svg" width="80"/> <strong>7 of Hearts (Copas)</strong></p></item>
        <item><p><media type="image" src="figures/ace_of_spades.svg" width="80"/> <strong>Ace of Spades (Espadilha)</strong></p></item>
        <item><p><media type="image" src="figures/7_of_diamonds.svg" width="80"/> <strong>7 of Diamonds (Pica-fumo)</strong></p></item>
    </list>
    <p>Followed by standard cards: 3 > 2 > 1 (except A♠) > 12 > 11 > 10 > 7 (except 7♥, 7♦) > 6 > 5 > 4 (except 4♣).</p>
  </section>
</page>
